{"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoding","doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoders","doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecodingError","doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecodingContext","doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoderRegistry"],"title":"Decoding","generated":true,"anchor":"Decoding"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"ImageDecoding Protocol","type":"heading","anchor":"ImageDecoding-Protocol"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"At the core of the decoding infrastructure is the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoding"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["public protocol ImageDecoding {","    \/\/\/ Produces an image from the given image data.","    func decode(_ data: Data) -> ImageContainer?","","    \/\/\/ Produces an image from the given partially downloaded image data.","    \/\/\/ This method might be called multiple times during a single decoding","    \/\/\/ session. When the image download is complete, `decode(data:)` method is called.","    \/\/\/","    \/\/\/ - returns: nil by default.","    func decodePartiallyDownloadedData(_ data: Data) -> ImageContainer?","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageContainer"},{"type":"text","text":" is a struct that wraps the decoded image and (optionally) the original data and some additional information. The decoder decides what to attach to the container."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["public struct ImageContainer {","    \/\/ Either `UIImage` or `NSImage`, depending on the platform.","    public let image: UIImage","    public let data: Data?","    public let userInfo: [AnyHashable: Any]","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When the first chunk of the image data is loaded, "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImagePipeline"},{"type":"text","text":" creates a decoder for the given image format."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The pipeline uses "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoderRegistry"},{"type":"text","text":" to find the decoder.  The decoder is created once and is reused across a single image decoding session until the final chunk of data is downloaded. If the decoder supports progressive decoding, make it a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":" to retain state within a single decoding session."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoding\/decode(_:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" method only passes "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"data"},{"type":"text","text":" to the decoder. If the decoder needs additional information, pass it when instantiating it. "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecodingContext","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" provides everything that you might need."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can also take advantage of "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageRequest\/userInfo","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". For example, you may pass the target image view size to the SVG decoder to let it know the size of the image to create."}]}],"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The decoding is performed in the background on the operation queue provided in "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImagePipeline\/Configuration-swift.struct"},{"type":"text","text":". There is always only one decoding request at a time. The pipeline doesn’t call "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoding\/decodePartiallyDownloadedData(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" again until you are finished with the previous chunk."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Registering Decoders","anchor":"Registering-Decoders"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To register the decoders, use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoderRegistry"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["func register() {","    ImageDecoderRegistry.shared.register(ImageDecoders.SVG.init)","}","","extension ImageDecoders {","    final class SVG: ImageDecoding {","        init?(context: ImageDecodingContext) {","            guard context.isCompleted else {","                return nil \/\/ No progressive decoding","            }","","            let isSVG = context.urlResponse?.url?.absoluteString.hasSuffix(\".svg\") ?? false","            guard isSVG else {","                return nil \/\/ Image format isn't supported.","            }   ","        }","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"aside","name":"Tip","style":"tip","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To determine image type, use an ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/AssetType","type":"reference"},{"text":" initializer that takes data as input. ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/AssetType","type":"reference"},{"text":" represents uniform type identifiers or UTI.","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you register a decoder, you have access to "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecodingContext"},{"type":"text","text":" for the given decoding session."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Rendering Engines","anchor":"Rendering-Engines"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The decoders in Nuke work at download time - regular decoders produce images as data arrives, while progressive decoders can produce multiple previews before delivering the final images. But there are scenarios when decoding at download time doesn’t work: for example, for animated images."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For animated images, it is not feasible to decode all of the frames and put them in memory as bitmaps at download time – it will consume too much memory. You have to postpone decoding to rendering time. When the image is displayed, a rendering engine, like "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/kaishin\/Gifu"},{"type":"text","text":" or others, will decode and cache image frames on demand."}]},{"type":"aside","name":"Note","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"GIF is not an efficient format. It is recommended to use short MP4 clips instead. See ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/kean\/NukeDemo","type":"reference"},{"text":" for an example.","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Built-In Image Decoders","anchor":"Built-In-Image-Decoders"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can find all of the built-in decoders in the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoders"},{"type":"text","text":" namespace."}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"ImageDecoders.Default","anchor":"ImageDecodersDefault"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoders\/Default"},{"type":"text","text":" is used by default if no custom decoders are registered. It uses native "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIImage(data:)"},{"type":"text","text":" (and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSImage(data:)"},{"type":"text","text":") initializers to create images from data."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The default "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoders\/Default"},{"type":"text","text":" also supports progressively decoding JPEG. It produces a new preview every time it encounters a new frame."}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"ImageDecoders.Video","anchor":"ImageDecodersVideo"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Generates a video preview and attaches downloaded data to the image container."}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"ImageDecoders.Empty","anchor":"ImageDecodersEmpty"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoders\/Empty"},{"type":"text","text":" returns an empty placeholder image and attaches image data to the image container. It could also be configured to return partially downloaded data. "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoders\/Empty"},{"type":"text","text":" can be used when the rendering engine works directly with image data."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"Nuke"}],"title":"Image Decoding","role":"article","roleHeading":"Article"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/nuke\/image-decoding"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/image-decoding","interfaceLang